<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFB9FFE36DC2FBD7FC91AF7F" pageId="29" pageNumber="1542" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFB9FFE36DC2FBD7FC91AF7F" blockId="29.[178,1085,1098,1149]" pageId="29" pageNumber="1542">
Diagnosis: This is the only member of 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FFB9FFE36FF8FBD7FC99AF5D" authorityName="CHEVROLAT. Part" authorityYear="1834" box="[648,780,1098,1119]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Platynoptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="1555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66B1D019FFB9FFE36FF8FBD7FC99AF5D" box="[648,780,1098,1119]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="1542">Platynoptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that has a broad flavotestaceous streak that extends backwards from the humeral angle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFB9FFE36DC2FB11FCE4AEC5" pageId="29" pageNumber="1542" type="description">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFB9FFE36DC2FB11FCE4AEC5" blockId="29.[178,1085,1164,1479]" pageId="29" pageNumber="1542">
Description: Size: Length 12.0 mm; width 4.0 mm. Form: As in 
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFFB9FFE36EEAFB11FC67AFA0" box="[922,1010,1164,1186]" captionStart="Figs 161-164" captionStartId="52.[178,218,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-59@52.[178,1085,212,1498]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Figs 161-164: Habitus illustrations of (161) Pilosirus fasciatus, holotype; (162) P. versus, holotype; (163) Platynoptera carti, holotype; (164) Platynoptera flavohumeralis, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282519/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="1542">Fig. 164</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium mostly black, vertex with small flavotestaceous streak: clypeus flavotestaceous; pronotum bicolorous, lower sides and center of disc black, upper sides and triangular portion extending back from anterior margin flavotestaceous; mesoscutellum black; elytra bicolorous, mostly black, flavotestaceous behind humerus, with postmedial flavotestaceous fascia. Head: Antennal capitulum long (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFFB9FFE36FCDFA82FC9FAE37" box="[701,778,1311,1333]" captionStart="Figs 70-80" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1351,1373]" captionTargetBox="[178,1100,235,1309]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1100,212,1333]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 70-80: Antennae. (70) Isoforma fritilla, female; (71) I. goryi, female; (72) Isoforma planata, female; (73) Pilosirus brunoi, male; (74) Isoforma subgilva, female; (75) Pilosirus amazonicus, female; (76) P. fasciatus, female; (77) Platynoptera carti, male; (78) P. flavohumeralis, male; (79) P. humeralis, male; (80) P. lyciformis, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5294864" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5294864/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="1542">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
), basal capitular antennomere longer than combined length of funicular antennomeres; antennal carina very prominent; EW/FW 20/20. Thorax: Pronotum elongate, anterior margin not projected at middle, side margin of disc with shallow tubercle; PW/PL 60/70; elytral not strongly explanate at sides, carina faintly visible; EL/EW 270/70. Abdomen: Male pygidium not incised at distal margin; Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFFB9FFE36CC6FA2CFDDEAEC5" box="[438,587,1457,1479]" captionStart="Figs 109-132" captionStartId="39.[178,217,1439,1461]" captionTargetBox="[227,1033,212,1425]" captionTargetId="figure-1@39.[197,1067,212,1430]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Figs 109-132: Aedeagi. (109) Ambonoides retinoides phallus; (110) A. retinoides tegmen; (111) A. caraguata phallus; (112) A. caraguata tegmen; (113) Artoadenus dius phallus; (114) A. dius tegmen; (115) A. regina phallus; (116) A. regina tegmen; (117) Aspitonis alarutinis phallus; (118) A. alarutinis tegmen; (119) A. chiapas phallus; (120) A. chiapas tegmen; (121) A. undulicornis phallus; (122) A. undulicornis tegmen; (123) Isoforma biguttula phallus; (124) I. biguttula tegmen; (125) Platynoptera carti phallus; (126) P. carti tegmen; (127) P. flavohumeralis phallus; (128) P. flavohumeralis tegmen; (129) P.humeralis phallus; (130) P. humeralis tegmen;(131)P.lyciformis phallus;(132)P.lyciformis tegmen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297822" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297822/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="1542">Figs. 127, 128</figureCitation>
); phallic apex subacuminate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFB9FFE36DC2FA4BFEA3AD08" pageId="29" pageNumber="1542" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFB9FFE36DC2FA4BFEA3AD08" blockId="29.[178,1085,1494,1546]" pageId="29" pageNumber="1542">
